1. Problem Statement 

    Imagine we are working in large e-ecommrece company 

    Every second many users are doing diffrent activities on the website or mobile apps

        - Logging in 
        - Seaching produncts 
        - viewing product pages 
        - adding items to cart 
        - making payments 
        - logging out 

    At the same time the backend system is also generating technical activity such as :
        - API calls 
        - Warning 
        - errors 
        - Payment failure 
        - Authentication failure 
        - slow response 


    -- Logs files 


    The Main Problem:

    1. Too many login failure 

        - Some users are failing login again and again this may idicates:
            - wrong pasword attemps
            - brute froce attack 
            - suspicisous ativity 

    2. Repeated Payment Failure 
        
        - Some users are trying payments multiple times, but payments are failing :

            - Farud attemps 
            - Payment gateway issue 
            - bot traffic 


    3. Slow APIs 

        - Some Apis are taking too much time to respond 

    4. Suspicious IP address 
        
        - Some Ips are sending too many requests or are already blocked.


Why this is difficult :

    - Thoudands of records come every second
    - data can grow GBs or TBs 
    - manual analysis is impossible 
    - Excel or python loops are not enough 

Why Are we trying to Build:

    We are trying to build a mini log analytics and answer important business questions.


We want:

    - Fraud/ suspicious activity 

        - Users with too many failed login 
        - Users with repeted payment failures 
        - backlisted IP usages 
        - Suapicious repeted requests 

    - API health issues 

        - slow Apis 
        - Failing APis 
        - heavily used Apis 

    - User and system insights 

        - Most active users 
        - most common action 
        - error count
        - suspicious pattern 

        
    